1
00:00:22,366 --> 00:00:24,266
♪ I THINK IT'S TIME
WE BLOW THIS SCENE ♪

2
00:00:24,266 --> 00:00:26,600
♪ GET EVERYBODY
AND THEIR STUFF TOGETHER ♪

3
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:30,300
♪ OK, 3, 2, 1,
LET'S JAM ♪

4
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:51,141
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

5
00:01:51,807 --> 00:01:54,341
[BUBBLING]

6
00:02:31,882 --> 00:02:32,882
AAH!

7
00:02:32,882 --> 00:02:36,915
[PANTING]

8
00:02:36,915 --> 00:02:39,448
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

9
00:03:04,348 --> 00:03:05,482
HMM.

10
00:03:05,482 --> 00:03:07,015
[DOG WHINES AND BARKS]

11
00:03:07,015 --> 00:03:08,982
[PANTING]

12
00:03:08,982 --> 00:03:11,115
[CHUCKLES]

13
00:03:13,115 --> 00:03:15,915
[DOG WHINING]

14
00:03:17,115 --> 00:03:18,548
UM!

15
00:03:18,548 --> 00:03:19,348
[PANTING]

16
00:03:19,348 --> 00:03:21,148
IF YOU DON'T WORK,
YOU DON'T EAT.

17
00:03:21,148 --> 00:03:22,515
YOU'RE A HUNTING DOG.

18
00:03:22,515 --> 00:03:24,848
HUNT UP SOME FOOD.

19
00:03:25,348 --> 00:03:26,548
WE GIRLS ARE DIFFERENT.

20
00:03:26,548 --> 00:03:30,882
WE HAVE TO BE PAMPERED BECAUSE
WE'RE DELICATE AND REFINED.

21
00:03:30,882 --> 00:03:33,915
[SLURPING]

22
00:03:33,915 --> 00:03:35,815
MMMMM.

23
00:03:38,115 --> 00:03:39,982
HMM.

24
00:03:40,182 --> 00:03:42,215
3 MILLION WOOLONG REWARD?

25
00:03:42,215 --> 00:03:46,215
WELL, I'LL JUST HAVE
THE BOYS GET IT FOR ME, THEN.

26
00:03:47,448 --> 00:03:48,482
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

27
00:03:48,482 --> 00:03:51,148
DAMN, THAT BLUES
HARP SOUNDS SWEET.

28
00:03:51,148 --> 00:03:51,882
I KNEW IT WOULD.

29
00:03:51,882 --> 00:03:54,848
HMM! I THOUGHT
YOU LIKED JAZZ.

30
00:03:54,848 --> 00:03:56,248
DON'T BE DENSE.

31
00:03:56,248 --> 00:03:57,415
I STARTED WAILING THE BLUES

32
00:03:57,415 --> 00:03:59,315
WHEN THE DOCTOR
WHACKED MY BOTTOM

33
00:03:59,315 --> 00:04:00,915
ON THE DAY I WAS BORN.

34
00:04:00,915 --> 00:04:03,415
A BABY HIPSTER... VERY COOL.

35
00:04:03,415 --> 00:04:05,882
[BEEPING]

36
00:04:05,882 --> 00:04:09,215
NO DOUBT ABOUT IT,
IT'S GIRAFFE.

37
00:04:09,215 --> 00:04:09,882
ALL RIGHT.

38
00:04:09,882 --> 00:04:11,815
I'M GOING IN FROM THE RIGHT.

39
00:04:11,815 --> 00:04:13,115
YOU TAKE THE LEFT SIDE.

40
00:04:13,115 --> 00:04:15,282
LARD BOY IS IN THE WAY.

41
00:04:15,282 --> 00:04:18,248
HMM? OH!

42
00:04:18,248 --> 00:04:19,248
THAT'S FATTY.

43
00:04:19,248 --> 00:04:21,515
MAKE A MOVE, JET.
THE BALL'S IN YOUR COURT.

44
00:04:21,515 --> 00:04:24,248
HMM.

45
00:04:24,248 --> 00:04:25,848
YO! HEY, FATTY!

46
00:04:25,848 --> 00:04:26,982
- HUH?
- FATTY RIVER!

47
00:04:26,982 --> 00:04:30,215
- LONG TIME NO SEE, BUDDY!
- OH! WHO'D HAVE GUESSED?

48
00:04:30,215 --> 00:04:31,482
IF IT ISN'T JET BLACK.

49
00:04:31,482 --> 00:04:34,915
WELL, WELL. WHEN THE HELL
DID YOU BLOW IN?

50
00:04:34,915 --> 00:04:35,615
HOW ABOUT YOU?

51
00:04:35,615 --> 00:04:36,615
YOU'RE LOOKING PRETTY CHEERY.

52
00:04:36,615 --> 00:04:39,215
WHAT HAPPENED?
DID YOU CATCH A NICE BIG ONE?

53
00:04:39,215 --> 00:04:41,315
[BOTH LAUGHING]

54
00:04:41,315 --> 00:04:45,082
I HAD NO IDEA YOU WERE
A FAN OF THE BLUES, FATTY.

55
00:04:45,082 --> 00:04:46,248
YOU KIDDING ME?

56
00:04:46,248 --> 00:04:47,082
I LISTENED TO THE BLUES

57
00:04:47,082 --> 00:04:49,182
WHEN I WAS STILL
IN MY FATHER'S SACK,

58
00:04:49,182 --> 00:04:50,515
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

59
00:04:50,515 --> 00:04:52,782
[BOTH LAUGHING]

60
00:05:13,248 --> 00:05:15,882
[NO AUDIO]

61
00:05:24,148 --> 00:05:26,182
UNH!
UH, SORRY.

62
00:05:26,182 --> 00:05:28,182
HEY!

63
00:05:36,282 --> 00:05:38,948
[DING]

64
00:05:44,115 --> 00:05:45,915
[TONE SOUNDS]

65
00:05:56,915 --> 00:05:58,348
HMPH!

66
00:06:06,148 --> 00:06:09,282
GIVE IT BACK NOW!

67
00:06:10,282 --> 00:06:12,115
ZEBRA!

68
00:06:13,148 --> 00:06:15,148
YAAH!

69
00:06:17,615 --> 00:06:19,148
[GASPS]

70
00:06:47,482 --> 00:06:50,182
HEY, YOU! WAKE UP!

71
00:06:50,182 --> 00:06:51,815
HEY!

72
00:06:51,815 --> 00:06:52,515
AW, GREAT.

73
00:06:52,515 --> 00:06:54,315
YOU DIE, AND I LOSE THE REWARD.

74
00:06:54,315 --> 00:06:57,348
DON'T... DON'T
BE FOOLED BY HIM...

75
00:06:57,348 --> 00:06:58,815
BY THE WAY HE LOOKS.

76
00:06:58,815 --> 00:07:01,248
DON'T TALK!
TRY TO STAY ALIVE!

77
00:07:01,248 --> 00:07:03,182
NOT ME.

78
00:07:03,182 --> 00:07:05,382
HE NEEDS HELP NOW.

79
00:07:05,382 --> 00:07:07,315
HELP HIM.

80
00:07:08,215 --> 00:07:11,848
THIS STONE...

81
00:07:14,015 --> 00:07:16,882
[SIRENS WAILING]

82
00:07:16,882 --> 00:07:18,215
WAIT!

83
00:07:18,215 --> 00:07:21,115
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

84
00:07:35,248 --> 00:07:36,982
[BEEP]

85
00:07:40,148 --> 00:07:41,882
[BEEPING]

86
00:07:43,415 --> 00:07:44,315
HMM.

87
00:07:44,315 --> 00:07:46,282
I CAN'T BE SURE
UNTIL I RUN ALL THE TESTS,

88
00:07:46,282 --> 00:07:49,315
BUT THIS MAY BE WORTH
A HEFTY SUM.

89
00:07:49,315 --> 00:07:51,182
SO WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO DO WITH IT?

90
00:07:51,182 --> 00:07:52,448
I HAVE NO IDEA.

91
00:07:52,448 --> 00:07:54,182
THE GUY GIVES IT
TO ME ON HIS OWN,

92
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:55,248
THEN HE DIES ON HIS OWN.

93
00:07:55,248 --> 00:07:57,915
I DON'T SEE ANY REASON
WHY WE SHOULDN'T KEEP IT.

94
00:07:57,915 --> 00:07:59,348
THERE IS NO REASON.

95
00:07:59,348 --> 00:08:02,348
YOU'RE NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR THAT KID, AFTER ALL.

96
00:08:02,348 --> 00:08:03,282
GIVE ME THAT!
HMM.

97
00:08:03,282 --> 00:08:06,248
THIS THING IS GOING
TO PAY FOR OUR FOOD.

98
00:08:06,248 --> 00:08:07,948
OUR FOOD, NOT YOURS.

99
00:08:07,948 --> 00:08:10,315
YOU KNOW, I THINK YOUR
HEART'S MADE OUT OF LEAD.

100
00:08:10,315 --> 00:08:13,248
NOT LIKE ME.
I'M A NICE GUY.

101
00:08:13,248 --> 00:08:14,282
I HAVE A GIFT FOR YOU.

102
00:08:14,282 --> 00:08:17,348
YAY!
ALL RIGHT, WHAT IS IT?

103
00:08:18,415 --> 00:08:20,282
AN OFFICIAL INVOICE?

104
00:08:20,282 --> 00:08:21,515
AN INVOICE FOR WHAT?

105
00:08:21,515 --> 00:08:23,415
ALL THE EXPENSES
YOU'VE RACKED UP

106
00:08:23,415 --> 00:08:25,148
SINCE YOU'VE BEEN ON OUR SHIP.

107
00:08:25,148 --> 00:08:26,815
AND THANKS FOR YOUR BUSINESS.

108
00:08:26,815 --> 00:08:29,948
YEAH. GREAT. ANYTIME.

109
00:08:30,182 --> 00:08:33,915
WHY DO YOU WANT
TO KNOW ABOUT THIS DEAD GUY?

110
00:08:33,915 --> 00:08:34,748
WELL, UH...

111
00:08:34,748 --> 00:08:39,115
HA! SO YOU WERE
AFTER GIRAFFE, TOO.

112
00:08:39,115 --> 00:08:41,982
DID YOU GET A GOOD DEAL?

113
00:08:41,982 --> 00:08:42,748
HMM?

114
00:08:42,748 --> 00:08:45,415
[CHUCKLES]
ENJOYING THE SWEETS?

115
00:08:45,415 --> 00:08:46,215
I ALWAYS DO.

116
00:08:46,215 --> 00:08:48,482
THERE'S NO BOUNTY IN IT,
YOU KNOW.

117
00:08:48,482 --> 00:08:49,348
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

118
00:08:49,348 --> 00:08:51,315
THERE'S NOTHING TO
GAIN HERE AT ALL.

119
00:08:51,315 --> 00:08:53,048
HMM.
NO, I MEAN IT.

120
00:08:53,048 --> 00:08:54,482
THERE'S NOTHING
ON THE LINE HERE.

121
00:08:54,482 --> 00:08:55,915
YEAH, RIGHT, JET.

122
00:08:55,915 --> 00:08:58,115
YOU'RE GOING TO OWE
ME ONE FOR TODAY.

123
00:08:58,115 --> 00:08:59,115
ALL RIGHT.
YOU KNOW THAT KID

124
00:08:59,115 --> 00:09:01,382
ON THE BLUES HARP
THE OTHER DAY? NAME'S WEN.

125
00:09:01,382 --> 00:09:05,415
GIRAFFE WAS AFTER
THE KID'S SO-CALLED FATHER,

126
00:09:05,415 --> 00:09:07,248
AN OLD FRIEND.
HE GOES BY THE NAME ZEBRA.

127
00:09:07,248 --> 00:09:08,048
THEY WERE FRIENDS?

128
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:10,148
SHEESH!
YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW THAT?

129
00:09:10,148 --> 00:09:11,282
THE TWO OF THEM WERE THE LEADERS

130
00:09:11,282 --> 00:09:13,115
OF THE SELF-DEFENSE
VOLUNTEER SQUAD.

131
00:09:13,115 --> 00:09:16,315
THEY WORKED TOGETHER
UNTIL ABOUT 10 YEARS AGO.

132
00:09:16,315 --> 00:09:19,148
I DON'T GET IT.

133
00:09:19,148 --> 00:09:21,282
WHY WAS HE AFTER AN OLD COMRADE?

134
00:09:21,282 --> 00:09:24,115
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

135
00:09:24,115 --> 00:09:26,148
10 YEARS AGO,
THEY HAD A CONFRONTATION

136
00:09:26,148 --> 00:09:30,248
WITH SOME SPACE RAIDERS
A LAND DISPUTE.

137
00:09:30,248 --> 00:09:34,548
IT ALL CAME DOWN AT SOME
R&D FACILITY NEAR MARS.

138
00:09:34,548 --> 00:09:38,915
A FEW DAYS LATER,
THE RAIDERS ARE WIPED OUT,

139
00:09:38,915 --> 00:09:39,882
ZEBRA IS MISSING,

140
00:09:39,882 --> 00:09:43,882
AND GIRAFFE IS FOUND
BLINDFOLDED IN A SILO.

141
00:09:43,882 --> 00:09:46,315
THEY SAY ZEBRA
DOUBLE-CROSSED HIM

142
00:09:46,315 --> 00:09:48,148
SO HE COULD RUN THE SQUAD SOLO.

143
00:09:48,148 --> 00:09:52,915
LATER, ZEBRA TURNS UP
IN A WHEELCHAIR WITH THE KID.

144
00:09:52,915 --> 00:09:57,115
GUESS IT DIDN'T TURN OUT
THE WAY HE PLANNED.

145
00:09:57,115 --> 00:09:59,848
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

146
00:10:01,582 --> 00:10:02,648
SO THE BOTTOM LINE IS,

147
00:10:02,648 --> 00:10:06,215
GIRAFFE WAS KILLED OFF
OVER SOME INTERNAL POLITICS.

148
00:10:06,215 --> 00:10:08,415
BETRAYAL MAY COME
EASILY TO WOMEN,

149
00:10:08,415 --> 00:10:11,082
BUT MEN LIVE BY
IRON CODES OF HONOR.

150
00:10:11,082 --> 00:10:12,148
YOU BELIEVE THAT?

151
00:10:12,148 --> 00:10:15,248
I'M TRYING TO, REAL HARD.

152
00:10:15,248 --> 00:10:18,182
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

153
00:10:26,848 --> 00:10:28,315
[HARMONICA STOPS]

154
00:10:43,482 --> 00:10:46,182
TELL ME... WHO ARE YOU?

155
00:10:46,182 --> 00:10:49,215
JUST SOME SUSPICIOUS GUY.

156
00:10:49,215 --> 00:10:50,582
WHAT DO YOU WANT HERE?

157
00:10:50,582 --> 00:10:53,082
BEFORE GIRAFFE
BOUGHT THE FARM,

158
00:10:53,082 --> 00:10:56,015
HE ASKED ME TO COME
HERE TO HELP YOU.

159
00:10:59,315 --> 00:11:01,548
BUT ZEBRA SHOT GIRAFFE.

160
00:11:01,548 --> 00:11:03,448
UHHUH.

161
00:11:03,448 --> 00:11:06,282
THEN WHY WOULD GIRAFFE
ASK HIM TO HELP THE KID?

162
00:11:06,282 --> 00:11:07,915
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

163
00:11:07,915 --> 00:11:10,448
HMM? HEY, THE KID'S
IN THE HEADLINES.

164
00:11:10,448 --> 00:11:13,215
GUESS HE MUST BE
PRETTY FAMOUS, HUH?

165
00:11:13,215 --> 00:11:14,082
YEAH.

166
00:11:14,082 --> 00:11:17,482
KID'S A GENIUS.
PLAYS LIKE AN OLD PRO.

167
00:11:17,482 --> 00:11:19,282
HMM?
[GASPS]

168
00:11:19,282 --> 00:11:20,148
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE!

169
00:11:20,148 --> 00:11:21,915
THIS GUY ISN'T ZEBRA.

170
00:11:21,915 --> 00:11:23,015
WHAT'S THAT?

171
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:25,915
LOOK CLOSE.
CAN'T YOU SEE THE DATE?

172
00:11:25,915 --> 00:11:26,948
WHAT THE HELL?!

173
00:11:26,948 --> 00:11:29,248
THIS WAS PUBLISHED 30 YEARS AGO.

174
00:11:29,248 --> 00:11:32,282
HOW CAN HE HAVE THE SAME FACE?

175
00:11:32,282 --> 00:11:32,982
COME ON.

176
00:11:32,982 --> 00:11:35,315
THERE'S NOTHING TO BE AFRAID OF.

177
00:11:35,315 --> 00:11:37,082
COME HERE. LET'S TALK.

178
00:11:37,082 --> 00:11:38,948
[GUNSHOT]
UNH!

179
00:11:39,382 --> 00:11:41,882
YOU'D BETTER STAY OUT OF IT.

180
00:11:41,882 --> 00:11:42,982
HUH?

181
00:11:42,982 --> 00:11:45,348
LITTLE TWERP LIKE YOU
STICKS HIS NECK OUT TOO FAR,

182
00:11:45,348 --> 00:11:48,415
HE'LL GET IT CUT OFF.
UNDERSTAND?

183
00:11:49,282 --> 00:11:51,182
AAH!

184
00:11:51,182 --> 00:11:52,548
DON'T GIVE ME THAT CRAP, KID!

185
00:11:52,548 --> 00:11:54,482
SORRY, BUT I'M NOT A KID.

186
00:11:54,482 --> 00:11:56,515
YEAH.
ALL KIDS SAY THAT.

187
00:11:56,515 --> 00:11:59,815
I KNOW WHAT I LOOK LIKE,

188
00:11:59,815 --> 00:12:02,915
BUT I WAS ALIVE
WHEN THIS PLACE WAS AN OUTPOST,

189
00:12:02,915 --> 00:12:05,448
BEFORE THE ASTEROIDS
WERE EVEN SETTLED.

190
00:12:05,448 --> 00:12:07,948
GET THE PICTURE?

191
00:12:26,849 --> 00:12:29,849
[BLUES HARMONICA PLAYING]

192
00:13:18,841 --> 00:13:21,174
[RUMBLING]

193
00:13:54,597 --> 00:13:58,830
THE HYPERSPACE GATE
HAD BLOWN TO BITS.

194
00:13:59,530 --> 00:14:04,397
FROM THAT DAY ON, MY BODY
COMPLETELY STOPPED AGING.

195
00:14:04,630 --> 00:14:05,830
I CAN'T DIE.

196
00:14:05,830 --> 00:14:08,530
THERE WAS ALWAYS
SOMEONE DISCOVERING ME,

197
00:14:08,530 --> 00:14:09,464
DOING EXPERIMENTS,

198
00:14:09,464 --> 00:14:12,097
BUT THEY ALL DIED,
AND I KEPT ON LIVING.

199
00:14:12,097 --> 00:14:13,230
THE END FOR THIS GUY STARTED

200
00:14:13,230 --> 00:14:16,964
WHEN HIS SELF-DEFENSE
VOLUNTEER SQUAD HIT OUR R&D LAB.

201
00:14:16,964 --> 00:14:17,830
I NEEDED A NEW COVER,

202
00:14:17,830 --> 00:14:20,164
SOMEONE TO PLAY
THE PART OF MY PARENT.

203
00:14:20,164 --> 00:14:23,897
DON'T... DON'T
BE FOOLED BY HIM...

204
00:14:23,897 --> 00:14:26,564
BY THE WAY HE LOOKS.

205
00:14:26,564 --> 00:14:28,397
NOT ME.

206
00:14:28,397 --> 00:14:30,997
HE NEEDS HELP NOW.

207
00:14:30,997 --> 00:14:33,464
HELP HIM.

208
00:14:35,797 --> 00:14:39,430
I THINK HE'S THE THIRD GUY
I'VE USED LIKE THIS.

209
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:41,964
NOW, WHERE'S THE RING?

210
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:42,930
RING?

211
00:14:42,930 --> 00:14:44,397
WHAT RING?

212
00:14:44,397 --> 00:14:45,164
[GUNSHOT]
UNH!

213
00:14:45,164 --> 00:14:47,564
THAT'S OK.
EVEN IF YOU HAD IT,

214
00:14:47,564 --> 00:14:51,564
IT'D JUST BE A CASE OF
CASTING PEARLS BEFORE SWINE.

215
00:14:51,564 --> 00:14:53,430
[COCKS GUN]
UNH!

216
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:55,797
[GUNFIRE]

217
00:15:04,030 --> 00:15:05,130
[RELOADS GUN]

218
00:15:05,130 --> 00:15:07,697
[GUNFIRE]

219
00:15:16,497 --> 00:15:17,430
[GUNSHOT]
UNH!

220
00:15:17,430 --> 00:15:19,597
[GUN CLATTERS TO FLOOR]

221
00:15:21,097 --> 00:15:22,830
[GUNSHOT]

222
00:15:30,964 --> 00:15:32,430
UNH!

223
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:35,864
[GUNFIRE]

224
00:15:37,630 --> 00:15:39,130
AAH!

225
00:15:39,997 --> 00:15:41,997
[CRASH]

226
00:16:03,430 --> 00:16:06,564
AW, QUIT COMPLAINING,
YOU BIG KLUTZ.

227
00:16:06,564 --> 00:16:10,097
YOU'RE LUCKY YOU GOT AWAY WITH
THIS LITTLE SCRATCH ON YOUR ARM.

228
00:16:10,097 --> 00:16:13,530
BUT WE DON'T HAVE THE MONEY
TO PAY FOR A FUNERAL.

229
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:15,397
I'M SORRY.

230
00:16:15,397 --> 00:16:16,830
HMM?

231
00:16:16,830 --> 00:16:18,797
HMM.

232
00:16:19,030 --> 00:16:20,897
[DOG BARKING]

233
00:16:20,897 --> 00:16:21,964
CAN IT, EIN!

234
00:16:21,964 --> 00:16:23,930
DON'T BE OBNOXIOUS.

235
00:16:23,930 --> 00:16:25,897
[DOG WHINING]

236
00:16:27,997 --> 00:16:29,664
HUH?

237
00:16:34,697 --> 00:16:36,830
HMM?

238
00:16:36,830 --> 00:16:40,530
JET... THE ALPHACATCH.

239
00:16:44,164 --> 00:16:47,564
[BEEPING]

240
00:16:47,564 --> 00:16:48,897
AW, CRAP.

241
00:16:48,897 --> 00:16:50,530
THIS PIECE OF JUNK!

242
00:16:50,530 --> 00:16:51,864
ALL RIGHT.

243
00:16:51,864 --> 00:16:55,864
NOW... WHAT DO YOU
MAKE OUT OF THIS?

244
00:16:58,964 --> 00:17:00,864
A HOTEL ROOM. THAT'S IT.

245
00:17:00,864 --> 00:17:03,830
HE'S REMEMBERING THE TIME
GIRAFFE GOT BLOWN AWAY.

246
00:17:03,830 --> 00:17:05,564
GIVE IT BACK NOW!

247
00:17:05,564 --> 00:17:08,464
ZEBRA, COME OVER HERE! HURRY!

248
00:17:08,464 --> 00:17:09,164
DAMN.

249
00:17:09,164 --> 00:17:10,997
AND THEN WHAT?

250
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:13,930
COME ON, WHAT DID GIRAFFE SAY?

251
00:17:15,930 --> 00:17:16,997
I HAVE IT NOW.

252
00:17:16,997 --> 00:17:18,764
I CAN DO YOU IN WITH THIS.

253
00:17:18,764 --> 00:17:22,997
THIS STONE HAS THE POWER
TO RETURN TIME TO YOU.

254
00:17:23,930 --> 00:17:27,430
NOW, HAND ZEBRA OVER TO ME!

255
00:17:27,730 --> 00:17:29,530
ZEBRA!

256
00:17:29,530 --> 00:17:30,897
[GUNSHOT]

257
00:17:30,897 --> 00:17:33,930
[BLUES HARMONICA PLAYING]

258
00:17:56,097 --> 00:17:59,864
WHEN THE GATE EXPLODED,
A COORDINATE SYSTEM WAS CREATED

259
00:17:59,864 --> 00:18:01,864
FROM THE RESULTING
TWISTS IN HYPERSPACE

260
00:18:01,864 --> 00:18:05,597
A KIND OF SINGULARITY THAT
DREW IN VAST AMOUNTS OF ENERGY,

261
00:18:05,597 --> 00:18:09,864
ENCLOSING AND CRYSTALLIZING
THEM INTO A SINGLE-FACETED STONE

262
00:18:09,864 --> 00:18:12,864
THE GEM THAT MAKES UP THIS RING.

263
00:18:13,897 --> 00:18:16,697
THE SAME ENERGY BROKE
WEN'S CIRCADIAN RHYTHM.

264
00:18:16,697 --> 00:18:18,797
HIS PINEAL BODY
CONTINUALLY PRODUCES

265
00:18:18,797 --> 00:18:21,097
A SUBSTANCE LIKE MELATONIN

266
00:18:21,097 --> 00:18:22,830
THAT INHIBITS AGING.

267
00:18:22,830 --> 00:18:25,797
THAT'S THE THEORY IN A NUTSHELL.

268
00:18:25,797 --> 00:18:27,130
GET THE PICTURE?

269
00:18:27,130 --> 00:18:28,630
YEAH, AS IF.

270
00:18:28,630 --> 00:18:29,764
HMM.
I DON'T, EITHER,

271
00:18:29,764 --> 00:18:33,664
WHICH SIMPLY MEANS...
THERE'S NO WAY TO KNOW FOR SURE

272
00:18:33,664 --> 00:18:37,897
UNTIL WE STICK THE GEM
INTO THE KID AND FIND OUT.

273
00:18:40,864 --> 00:18:42,564
ANYTHING COULD HAPPEN.

274
00:18:42,564 --> 00:18:45,530
IT COULD BLOW SKYHIGH
THE MOMENT IT HITS.

275
00:18:45,530 --> 00:18:48,964
KIND OF MAKES IT INTERESTING.

276
00:18:57,697 --> 00:18:58,497
YES, MY DEAR?

277
00:18:58,497 --> 00:18:59,597
I JUST THOUGHT
I'D SAY GOODBYE, SPIKE,

278
00:18:59,597 --> 00:19:02,764
SINCE I'M SURE IT'S THE LAST
TIME I'LL BE SEEING YOU.

279
00:19:02,764 --> 00:19:04,897
HUH! YOU MEAN,
YOU'RE FINALLY LEAVING US?

280
00:19:04,897 --> 00:19:08,564
NO! I MEAN YOU'RE
NOT COMING BACK.

281
00:19:10,897 --> 00:19:12,730
[FLICKS LIGHTER]

282
00:19:13,030 --> 00:19:14,730
[CLICK]

283
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:18,597
I DON'T LIKE THIS SETUP, JET.

284
00:19:18,597 --> 00:19:21,364
DON'T LIKE IT AT ALL.

285
00:19:29,732 --> 00:19:32,799
MEN ARE SUCH TOTAL IDIOTS.

286
00:19:46,453 --> 00:19:49,153
[GUNSHOT]
[WINDOW SHATTERS]

287
00:19:49,153 --> 00:19:53,020
[DOG BARKING]

288
00:20:11,528 --> 00:20:16,361
[GUNFIRE]
[TIRES SQUEALING]

289
00:20:41,361 --> 00:20:46,594
[GUNSHOTS]

290
00:20:59,494 --> 00:21:01,261
[GUNSHOT]

291
00:21:04,661 --> 00:21:06,528
[GASPS]

292
00:21:11,128 --> 00:21:12,494
[GASPS]

293
00:21:41,261 --> 00:21:45,428
[GASPING AND MOANING]

294
00:21:54,094 --> 00:21:57,461
UH, UH...

295
00:21:57,461 --> 00:21:58,642
I SEE.

296
00:21:58,642 --> 00:22:01,743
YES, I CAN FINALLY DIE AT LAST.

297
00:22:01,743 --> 00:22:05,276
UH, I FEEL SO HEAVY...

298
00:22:05,276 --> 00:22:11,676
UH... BUT I FEEL
I FINALLY FEEL AT EASE.

299
00:22:11,676 --> 00:22:14,443
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

300
00:22:15,543 --> 00:22:20,843
DO YOU UNDERSTAND? DO YOU?

301
00:22:28,910 --> 00:22:32,610
[BLOWS INTO HARMONICA]

302
00:22:34,610 --> 00:22:37,843
YEAH, I UNDERSTAND.

303
00:22:37,843 --> 00:22:40,110
AS IF.

304
00:22:49,876 --> 00:22:51,876
BANG.

305
00:24:35,366 --> 00:24:37,646
[SPEECH INAUDIBLE
OVER LOUD ROCK MUSIC]

306
00:24:37,646 --> 00:24:39,366
YOU KNOW WHAT
HEAVY METAL IS, RIGHT?

307
00:24:39,366 --> 00:24:41,433
WHAT DID YOU SAY?
HEAVY METAL!

308
00:24:41,433 --> 00:24:42,566
I SAID, HEAVY METAL!

309
00:24:42,566 --> 00:24:43,633
WHAT?!
I CAN'T HEAR YOU!

310
00:24:43,633 --> 00:24:46,366
HEY! CAN YOU DO SOMETHING
ABOUT ALL THAT NOISE?

311
00:24:46,366 --> 00:24:48,700
IT'S GOING TO BE RUNNING
THROUGH THE WHOLE NEXT EPISODE.

312
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:50,666
I THINK I'LL STAY
OUT OF IT, THEN!

313
00:24:50,666 --> 00:24:52,700
I CAN'T HEAR A WORD
YOU'RE SAYING!

314
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:54,666
NEXT EPISODE
HEAVY METAL QUEEN!

315
00:24:54,666 --> 00:24:57,233
IS THIS REALLY
GETTING THROUGH TO ANYONE?

